title: Metastatic Prostate Cancer  1
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was isolated with Trizol (Invitrogen Cat. No. 15596-026, Carlsbad, CA), according to the manufacturer's instructions. Total RNA was further purified using the Qiagen RNAeasy Mini Kit (Cat. No. 74104) according to the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
characteristics_ch2: Metastatic tissue from soft tissue, collected by warm autopsy
extract_protocol_ch2: Total RNA was isolated with Trizol (Invitrogen Cat. No. 15596-026, Carlsbad, CA), according to the manufacturer's instructions. Total RNA was further purified using the Qiagen RNAeasy Mini Kit (Cat. No. 74104) according to the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch2: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
hyb_protocol: 825ng of Cy3 and Cy5 labelled aRNA were hybridized competitively for 17 hrs in a 65 C hybridization oven (G2545A, Agilent) set to 10 rpm in a final concentration of 1X GEx Hybridization Buffer HI-RPM, according to the manufacturer's recommnded protocol (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent). Arrays were washed according to the manufacturer's recommended protocol including the Stabilization and Drying Solution step (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent).
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned at 5um resolution on an Agilent DNA Microarray Scanner (G2505B, Agilent) using the default settings for 1x44k format two-color arrays.
description: Metastatic tissue from soft tissue, collected by warm autopsy
data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (Version 9.1.3.1). Spot values were normalized using the default linear-lowess normalization. Samples M5a and M5b were isolated from the same patient and normalized values were averaged before data analysis.

label_protocol_ch1: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
extract_protocol_ch2: Total RNA was isolated with Trizol (Invitrogen Cat. No. 15596-026, Carlsbad, CA), according to the manufacturer's instructions. Total RNA was further purified using the Qiagen RNAeasy Mini Kit (Cat. No. 74104) according to the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch2: One ug of total RNA was reverse transcripted to cDNA using T7 Promoter Primer and MMLV-RT. Then the cDNA was converted to aRNA using T7 RNA polymerase, which simultaneously amplifies target material and incorporates cyanine 3- or cyanine 5-labeled CTP (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis Protocol, Agilent).
hyb_protocol: 825ng of Cy3 and Cy5 labelled aRNA were hybridized competitively for 17 hrs in a 65 C hybridization oven (G2545A, Agilent) set to 10 rpm in a final concentration of 1X GEx Hybridization Buffer HI-RPM, according to the manufacturer's recommnded protocol (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent). Arrays were washed according to the manufacturer's recommended protocol including the Stabilization and Drying Solution step (Two-Color Microarray-Based Gene Expression Analysis, Agilent).
scan_protocol: Arrays were scanned at 5um resolution on an Agilent DNA Microarray Scanner (G2505B, Agilent) using the default settings for 1x44k format two-color arrays.
data_processing: Images were auto gridded, analyzed and data extracted using Agilent Feature Extraction Software (Version 9.1.3.1). Spot values were normalized using the default linear-lowess normalization. Samples M5a and M5b were isolated from the same patient and normalized values were averaged before data analysis.
